<section id="Day1">
<a href="#Day1"><h2>Day1:Varanasi</h2></a>
<p>You are expected to arrive at Varanasi in the morning by train/flight. Upon arrival, you check in at the hotel and take some rest. Later you leave for local sightseeing, visit the Bharat Mata Mandir dedicated to Mother India; go around for some shopping and you can witness the evening sunset and the prayer offering rituals done along the banks. You return to the hotel and stay overnight.
</p>
</section> 
<section id="Day2">
<a href="#Day2"><h2>Day2:Varanasi - Allahabad</h2></a>
<p>After your breakfast, you will proceed to Allahabad which takes about 2 and a half hour to reach. On arrival, you can take a dip in the sacred spot of Triveni Sangam, a point where the three rivers meet. Visit Anand Bhawan and lying Hanuman temple. Later you return back to Varanasi, on the way you visit the Sitamadi and Vindhyachal temples. After reaching you can retire for the night.
</p>
</section>  
<section id="Day3">
<a href="#Day3"><h2>Day3: Varanasi</h2></a>
<p>In the morning you will go for a boat ride on Ganga and watch the sunrise, later you visit the Vishwanath Temple, Durga Temple, Tulsi Manas Mandir, Sarnath, and the University. The journey will come to an end with your return to your respective Stations and Airport.
</p>
